Joint EN+BM: cross-language merge rate
Run on the combined EN+BM pool, how often does C0 place an EN surface form and a BM surface form of the same act into one cluster? This is the direct, no-API probe of whether C0 bridges languages (e.g. Subsidi Bahan Api ↔︎ fuel subsidy). A low merge rate means C0 treats the languages as disjoint and cross-language aggregation needs a translation step.


