Headline: final-output consistency
The pipeline runs end-to-end on each language and produces a set of acts, each carrying a C2 motivation label, sign, and exogeneity. The question is whether the two runs land on the same fiscal reasoning. Pure marginals cannot answer this (identical totals can hide compensating per-act errors), so the headline is two timeline figures: for each year and language, acts are counted into motivation × sign cells and drawn as a diverging stacked bar — increases grow the bar upward, decreases downward, coloured by motivation, faceted by language. The reader compares the EN and BM rows directly.
The two figures differ only in the timing source: the first dates each act by the year extracted from its name (language-invariant numerals; partial coverage), the second by the source-document year (always present).

